						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into the floor in front of the Veṅkatēśvara temple in the village.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 123 • , Pushya ba. 8, Friday, Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Seems to register the grant of land for burning half a lamp to the temple of Janārdana.</p>						

						<p>Another fragment inscription in late characters appears to record the gift of money for erection of a pillar by an individual at the instance of dancer Gaṁggasāni.</p>						

						</summary>
